Privacy Policy for Discord Bot - Alphacaard // EN

1. Introduction
Welcome to Alphacaard, the Discord bot ("Bot"). This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when using the Bot.

2. Information Collection
2.1. The Bot may collect the following information:

User and server IDs for technical functionality.

Messages or commands sent to the Bot to process requests.

2.2. We do not collect sensitive personal information such as full names, addresses, or financial details.

3. Use of Information
3.1. The collected information is used to:

Operate and improve the Bot’s performance.

Provide requested responses and functionalities.

3.2. We do not use the information for commercial or advertising purposes.

4. Data Storage and Protection
4.1. Data collected by the Bot is securely stored and accessible only by the developer.
4.2. Reasonable measures are implemented to protect data from unauthorized access, modification, or deletion.

5. Data Sharing
5.1. Your information will not be shared with third parties, except:

When required by law or a legal order.

To prevent fraud or protect our rights.

6. Data Retention
6.1. Collected data will be retained as long as necessary to provide the Bot’s services.
6.2. You can request the deletion of your data by contacting the developer.

7. User Rights
7.1. You have the following rights regarding your data:

Access the collected information.

Request correction or deletion of your data.

8. Updates to the Privacy Policy
8.1. This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically.
8.2. It is recommended to review this policy regularly to stay informed about changes.

9. Contact
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, contact us via Discord or the email provided by the developer.

10. Acceptance of Privacy Policy
By using Alphacaard, you confirm that you have read, understood, and agree to this Privacy Policy.
